# Minimal .dockerignore.
#
# We deliberately keep this short. An earlier longer version (see git
# history) had many `**/dist`, `**/.expo`, `**/.turbo`-style globs that
# exposed a BuildKit edge case where `COPY apps ./apps` and similar
# whole-directory copies failed with "failed to calculate checksum...
# not found" — see RAILWAY-LESSONS.md issue 13.
#
# If you need to add new exclusions, prefer specific paths over
# wildcards and verify the build succeeds before committing.

# Dependencies — Docker installs fresh inside the build
node_modules
**/node_modules

# VCS metadata — not needed inside the image
.git

# Local env — secrets come from Railway env vars at runtime
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# Force-include critical workspace files. Nothing above SHOULD match
# these, but defensive negations rule out any future "hmm,
# pnpm-lock.yaml is missing" mystery and double as a cache-buster
# (changing this file invalidates BuildKit's COPY layer key).
!pnpm-lock.yaml
!pnpm-workspace.yaml
!package.json
!.npmrc
